<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1980,2035]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,152,239]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="0" pageNumber="58">
Here the situation is not that clear. The male 
<typeStatus box="[625,718,1980,2003]" pageId="0" pageNumber="58">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[782,881,1980,2003]" name="Paraguay" pageId="0" pageNumber="58">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
in the Academy of Natural Sciences in Philadelphia (small and dark photos in OSF) as well as the detailed original description show some differences to Karabagâ€™s diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName box="[181,296,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Anisophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,296,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="59">Anisophya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as a sulcate fastigium and especially the median appendages or teeth on the cerci (but which could be similar in 
<taxonomicName box="[264,375,184,207]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Anisophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borellii">
<emphasis box="[264,375,184,207]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="59">A. borellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Rehn" box="[528,653,184,207]" pageId="1" pageNumber="60" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1907) Orthoptera of the families Tettigoniidae and Gryllidae from Sapucay, Paraguay. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia, 59, 370 - 395." type="journal article" year="1907">
Rehn 
<number box="[594,653,184,207]" pageId="1" pageNumber="59" value="1907.0">1907</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Since there are otherwise no major contradictions, the species can be moved under 
<taxonomicName box="[297,410,216,239]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Anisophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[297,410,216,239]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="59">Anisophya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well.
</paragraph>
